Practice is completed under the supervision of an instructor in the speciality as a teaching assistant for a BA course in the speciality, in which students can apply their foreign language skills and other competences, as well as their knowledge of European languages and cultures. Practice may last from two to four weeks (depending on whether students wish to receive 3 or 6 ECTS). The workload and timetable will be set up by the student, the department and supervisor. Students tasks may include supporting the instructors (communication with students, detecting plagiarism), providing assistance in either Moodle or other e-learning environment, giving feedback on different tasks, conducting seminar discussions, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop and deepen knowledge and skills necessary in professional careers and to create links between acquired knowledge and possibilities of applying it. Above all the aim is to introduce the specificities of teaching the speciality and give the students the opportunity to try teaching in a higher education context, providing support services for teaching, communicating with students and giving feedback on different tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have completed their practice can apply knowledge from their speciality in work situations, considering the social and cultural context; can apply acquired knowledge and skills in completing different work tasks; can analyze their activities in solving practical work-related questions in their speciality; have the experience of completing specific work tasks and plans and can evaluate the results of their work constructively.
